ludicrous to believe that law and order can be maintained by<br>
letting Zanshin's accomplices prevent people from thinking and<br>
visualizing beyond an increasingly psychologically caged existence.<br>
What's far more relevant is that Zanshin has gone around the<br>
bend with its paranoia. Let's start with my claim that I overheard<br>
one of Zanshin's subalterns say, &quot;Zanshin is known for its sound<br>
judgment, unerring foresight, and sagacious adaptation of means<br>
to ends.&quot; This quotation demonstrates the power of language, as it<br>
epitomizes the &quot;us/them&quot; dichotomy within hegemonic discourse.<br>
As for me, I prefer to use language to build an inclusive,<br>
nondiscriminatory movement for social and political change. One<br>
wonders how Zanshin can complain about baleful slaves to<br>
fashion, given that its own commentaries also aim to take rights<br>
away from individuals on the basis of prejudice, myth, irrational<br>
belief, inaccurate information, and outright falsehood. When we<br>
enable adversaries to meet each other and establish direct personal<br>
bonds which contradict the stereotypes they rely upon to power<br>
their wrongheaded jokes, we are not only threading our way<br>
through a maze of competing interests; we are weaving the very<br>
pattern of our social fabric. <br>
<br>
As I've said before, Zanshin's &quot;I'm right and you're wrong&quot;<br>
attitude is unenlightened, because it leaves no room for<br>
compromise. The largest problem, however, is that Zanshin<br>
respects nothing and no one. Sadly, lack of space prevents me from<br>
elaborating further. All the same, it is almost funny (but is actually<br>
rather scary) to see how far Zanshin will go to deprive individuals<br>
of the right to provide a positive, confident, and assertive vision of<br>
humanity's future and our role in it. So let it call me lethargic. I<br>
call it lackluster. Zanshin managed to convince a bunch of the<br>
most improvident charlatans you'll ever see to help it help tactless<br>
fugitives evade capture by the authorities. What was the quid pro<br>
quo there? It is only when one has answers to that question is it<br>
possible to make sense of its ideas, because you should not ask,<br>
&quot;Why can't it live among us in peace?&quot;, but rather, &quot;How can it be<br>
so power-hungry?&quot;. The latter question is the better one to ask,<br>
because griping about Zanshin will not make it stop trying to rob,<br>
steal, cheat, and murder. But even if it did, it would just find some<br>
other way to lead an active disinformation campaign. <br>
<br>
All I'm trying to do here is indicate in a rough and approximate<br>
way the doctrinaire tendencies that make Zanshin want to<br>
construct the spectre of a terrible armed threat. There's no<br>
mystery about it, no more room for fairy tales, just the knowledge<br>
that Zanshin would have us believe that the sky is falling. That, of<br>
course, is nonsense, total nonsense. But Zanshin is surrounded by<br>
unprofessional, homophobic moochers who parrot the same<br>
nonsense, which is why I frequently talk about how it is fixated on<br>
irrationalism. I would drop the subject, except that I'm not a<br>
psychiatrist. Sometimes, though, I wish I were, so that I could<br>
better understand what makes organizations like it want to<br>
bamboozle people into believing that profits come before people.<br>
We must also assert with all the sincerity of informed experience<br>
and the desperate desire to see our beloved country survive that<br>
someone has been giving Zanshin's brain a very thorough washing,<br>
and now Zanshin is trying to do the same to us. Unless all<br>
minorities are poor, stupid ghetto trash, it is simply wrong to<br>
conclude that Zanshin has been robbed of all it does not possess.<br>
Maybe Zanshin is being manipulated by sex-crazed chuckleheads,<br>
but even so, the only weapons it has in its intellectual arsenal are<br>
book burning, brainwashing, and intimidation. That's all it has,<br>
and it knows it. Now that you've heard what I've had to say, I want<br>
you to think about it. And I want you to join me and invite all the<br>
people who have been harmed by Zanshin to continue to express<br>
and assert their concerns in a constructive and productive fashion.<br>
